## Core Concepts

### Utility-First

```html
<!-- Traditional CSS approach -->
<div class="card">
  <h2 class="card-title">Hello</h2>
</div>

<!-- Tailwind utility approach -->
<div class="rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 bg-white">
  <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Hello</h2>
</div>
```

### Responsive Design

```html
<!-- Mobile-first: base → sm → md → lg → xl → 2xl -->
<div class="
  w-full        /* Mobile: full width */
  md:w-1/2      /* Tablet: half width */
  lg:w-1/3      /* Desktop: third width */
">
  Content
</div>
```

| Breakpoint | Min Width | CSS |
|------------|-----------|-----|
| `sm` | 640px | `@media (min-width: 640px)` |
| `md` | 768px | `@media (min-width: 768px)` |
| `lg` | 1024px | `@media (min-width: 1024px)` |
| `xl` | 1280px | `@media (min-width: 1280px)` |
| `2xl` | 1536px | `@media (min-width: 1536px)` |

### State Variants

```html
<!-- Hover, focus, active states -->
<button class="
  bg-blue-500
  hover:bg-blue-600
  focus:ring-2
  focus:ring-blue-300
  active:bg-blue-700
  disabled:opacity-50
  disabled:cursor-not-allowed
">
  Click me
</button>

<!-- Group hover -->
<div class="group">
  <h3 class="group-hover:text-blue-500">Title</h3>
  <p class="group-hover:text-gray-600">Description</p>
</div>

<!-- Peer states (sibling) -->
<input class="peer" type="checkbox" />
<label class="peer-checked:text-green-500">Checked!</label>
```

